Belgian qualifier Elise Mertens will play in her first WTA Tour final after a commanding 6-4, 6-0 win over Croatian Jana Fett at the Hobart International on Friday.The 21-year-old world No.127 needed only 70 minutes to advance in a dominant display against the No.340-ranked Fett.Mertens will face Romanian third seed Monica Niculescu in Saturday&#8217;s final.The world No.40 advanced after a viral illness forced Ukrainian Lesia Tsurenko to withdraw before their scheduled semi-final match.-AFP